HEADWORD: Terry
<hw>Ter"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of heavy colored
fabric, either all silk, or silk and worsted, or silk and cotton, often
called <xex>terry velvet</xex>, used for upholstery and
trimmings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

